    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "There's no need for `ObliqueParentHashes` because the attestation is for the block itself. `ObliqueParentHashes` is necessary for `AggregatedAttestation` because those attestations are not for the block itself. Its possible that the attestation is for a block on a different fork, at which point `ObliqueParentHashes` is necessary to construct the parent hashes. In this case, we can simply walk up the chain to construct the parent hashes.\r\n\r\n`JustifiedSlotNumber` can be gotten from the crystallized state.",
